                            <comment id="267092" author="adilger" created="Tue, 7 Apr 2020 22:10:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lai,&lt;br/&gt;
I think this problem of accessing a directory with offline stripes is already fixed?  Is there already a test for this?  If yes, then this should be linked to the patch that fixed the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If not, then test could do something like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;create striped directory&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;create 100 files in it&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe -m&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; all entries to determine which MDT each file is on&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;take one MDT offline&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;&lt;tt&gt;ls -l&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; directory to check that entries for online MDTs are still available&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;verify that none of the offline entries are listed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;verify that &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ls -l&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; returns an error at the end&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;take MDT online&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;verify that all files are accessible again.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
